---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="About - Jacob Weinbren"
	description="Web Developer, GIS Specialist, and Researcher based in Exeter"
>
	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">About Me</h1>

		<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6">
			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">
					Professional Overview
				</h2>
				<p>
					I'm a Full Stack Web Developer currently pursuing an MSc in
					Geographic Information Science at the University of Exeter.
					My expertise spans modern web technologies including
					Next.js, React, Svelte, and Astro, complemented by strong
					capabilities in data visualisation and geospatial analysis.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">
					Technical Expertise
				</h2>
				<p>
					My development journey encompasses both front-end and
					back-end technologies, with particular focus on creating
					accessible, high-performance web applications. I'm
					proficient in:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Modern frameworks (Next.js, React, Svelte, Astro)</li>
					<li>Cloud services (AWS Certified)</li>
					<li>Database management (MySQL, Redis)</li>
					<li>GIS and data visualisation</li>
					<li>CI/CD and DevOps practices</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">
					Notable Projects
				</h2>
				<p>
					I've led several significant projects that demonstrate my
					commitment to innovative solutions:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<strong
							>Hebrew Transliteration + Duolingo Flashcards:</strong
						> Led a global team in developing a neural network-powered
						transliteration system and creating over 4,000 interactive
						flashcards.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Electoral Visualisations:</strong> Developed comprehensive
						mapping solutions for Israeli elections and UK voting patterns,
						receiving recognition from prominent political analysts and
						academics.
					</li>
					<li>
						<strong>Canadian Census 2021:</strong> Created sophisticated
						geospatial visualisations handling millions of data points
						using Redis map server technology.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">
					Community Engagement
				</h2>
				<p>
					Beyond development, I'm actively involved in academic and
					community activities. I serve as treasurer of the
					Postgraduate Society at Exeter University and engage with
					the local Jewish university society. I maintain a blog
					discussing literature, programming, and politics, reflecting
					my commitment to continuous learning and knowledge sharing.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-600">Get in Touch</h2>
				<p>
					I'm always interested in new opportunities and
					collaborations. Whether you're looking to discuss a project,
					share ideas, or just connect, feel free to reach out via
					<a
						href="mailto:jacobweinbren@gmail.com"
						class="text-green-600 hover:text-green-700"
					>
						email
					</a> or find me on
					<a
						href="https://github.com/JacobWeinbren"
						class="text-green-600 hover:text-green-700"
					>
						GitHub
					</a>.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
